cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.CL 

This paper deals with emotion recognition using deep learning techniques and specifically focuses on utilizing multiple CNN features and RNN subnets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training and pre-training of models, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of audio and visual modalities for emotion recognition suggests the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the use of fusion techniques, which can be related to the sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for emotion recognition, which can be related to the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
